&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Read-only Memory (ROM) and Random Access Memory (RAM)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;Computer memory&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a generic term for all of the different types of data storage technology that a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;computer&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;may use, including &lt;strong&gt;RAM, ROM,&lt;/strong&gt; and flash&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;memory.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Computer&amp;nbsp;memory&amp;nbsp;is any physical device capable of storing information temporarily.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);  &quot;&gt;The acronym &lt;strong&gt;RAM&lt;/strong&gt; stems from the fact that data stored in random access memory can be accessed &amp;ndash; as the name suggests &amp;ndash; in any random order. Or, put another way, any random bit of data can be accessed just as quickly as any other bit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);  &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROM&lt;/strong&gt; stands for &lt;strong&gt;read-only memory&lt;/strong&gt;, and the name stems from the fact that while data can be read from this type of computer memory, data cannot normally be written to it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Memory devices utilize integrated circuits&amp;nbsp;and are used by operating systems, hardware, and software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

